<meta content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: It doesn&#39;t matter whether you love or hate guns; it&#39;s obvious that the US would be a safer place if there weren&#39;t thousands of them sold every day without background checks. Dan Gross, president of the Brady Campaign to Prevent Gun Violence, makes a passionate, personal appeal for something that more than 90 percent of Americans want: background checks for all gun sales. &quot;For every great movement around the world, there&#39;s a moment where you can look back and say, &#39;That&#39;s when things really started to change,&#39;&quot; Gross says. &quot;For the movement to end gun violence in America, that moment is here.&quot;" name="description" />
